postcontent:
Daisy Power line 'Dirty Harry Special' Model 44 Chrome CO2 Pistol.  The '44' was the only revolver ever manufactured and marketed by Daisy and was only sold for a short period of time. The model 144 was a limited edition nickel plated version with an 8" barrel.  Super Rare is the only words that can describe this Daisy Model 44 (144). This is the rarest and hardest to find of all of the Daisy pistols, out there. Daisy manufactured the Model 44 from 1987 to 2000, but this model the Model 144 only between 1989 and 1990. It is in nice working and cosmetic condition and comes with the original box and manual.  This gun is primarily metal, nickel plated with only the cylinder and handle covers made of plastic.  The quality is exceptional and has the look and feel of the real deal.  This gun is highly collectable.  Asking $80.00 but willing to consider offers.  REDACTED for questions.

title: For Sale:  U.S. Optics SN-4S 1-4X Semi-Automatic Rifle Scope
postcontent:
I hate to let this scope go because it has sentimental value to me but it will not mount on my newly acquired FNH Scar 16s so I really have no use for it.  As you can see by the pictures, it does have some use wear but this scope is a tank!  It was designed to withstand the rigors of the modern day battlefield and it has held up very well with U.S. soldiers and special forces.  Another plus is the lifetime warranty that comes with U.S. Optics scopes, regardless of whether or not you are the original owner.  I cannot say enough good things about this scope.

The U.S. Optics SN-4s is a terrific choice to mount on an AR-15 or similar semi-automatic rifle (will not mount on a FNH Scar 16s).  At 1x magnification, the user can shoot with both eyes open at point blank range and at the maximum 4x magnification, the user can rely upon precision shot placement at much longer ranges.  The fully multi-coated Schott glass lenses allow full transmission of 94.6% of available light, which when paired with the red illuminated reticle, makes them ideal for use from dawn until dusk.  The illuminated reticle is also adjustable via an 11 position rheostat to allow the user to adjust intensity.  Windage and elevation knobs are U.S. #1 5/8 MOA Slimline which are finger adjustable to allow for quick adjustments whenever the need arises.  Each U.S. Optics Rifle Scope is hand-built by one person to ensure that the utmost care is taken in producing a quality scope.

A great review can be found here (http://www.tactical-life.com/special-weapons/us-optics-sn-4s-scope/).

Specs:

Tube Diameter: 30mm
Objective Bell Diameter: 35mm
Ocular Bell Diameter: 47.2mm

Adjustment Click Value: 5/8 MOA
Eye Relief: 2.8"
Exit Pupil Diameter: 6.23mm

Field of View at 100 Yards: 
110' @ 1x
33' @ 4x

title: For Sale:  Collectible 1986 Marksman Plainsman Model 1049 BB pistol
postcontent:
The Plainsman was originally manufactured by Healthways in Compton, CA. In 1983, Healthways was purchased by Marksman (Huntington Beach, CA) who continued to manufacture the Plainsman BB pistol until 1987 under the Marksman name as the model 1049. The Marksman Plainsman utilizes 12 gram CO2 cylinders and has the same three-position power adjusting knob at the base of the grip. The cartridge piercing system is simple but effective using an over-sized knurled piercing knob. This sample of the Marksman Plainsman showed very consistent shot velocities and decent accuracy making it a respectable plinker. This gun is in very nice working and cosmetic condition and is very collectible.  Made primarily of metal is a heavier gun that offer the real feel of a luger.

A rocket-propelled grenade (often abbreviated RPG) is a shoulder-fired, anti-tank weapon system that fires rockets equipped with an explosive warhead. These warheads are affixed to a rocket motor and stabilized in flight with fins. Some types of RPG are reloadable, while others are single-use. RPGs, with the exception of self-contained versions, are loaded from the muzzle. RPGs with HEAT warheads are very effective against armored vehicles such as armored personnel carriers (APCs).
